<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947861>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–16. Left metapleura of different genera of Lasiochilinae showing the ostiolar peritreme and metapleural microsculpture. 1–2, Plochiocoris (350X and 1000X respectively); 3–5, Eusolenophora (350X, 1000X and 2000X); 6–9, two species of Lasiocolpus showing the small specific differences following a generic pattern: 6–7, L. minor (200X and 1000X) and 8–9, L. sinuaticollis (200X and 1000X); 10–12, Anaelia (200X, 1000X and 2000X); 13–14, Dilasia (200X, and 2000X); 15–16, Lasiochilus (200X, and 2000X)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947861/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947905>
    dc:description "FIGURES 132–136. D. punctipennis. Male. 132, Pronotum and foretibia showing the spines (Sp) on internal margin; 133, Scutellum and hemelytron; 134, Metasternum; 135, Copulatory spines (Csp); 136, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947905/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947913>
    dc:description "FIGURES 149–158. D. similis. Male. 149, Head; 150, Pronotum; 151, Foretibia showing the spines (Sp) on internal margin and pad (Fos); 152, Apical half of foretibia; 153, Spines on foretrochanter (Tsp); 154, Hemelytron; 155, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternum (Ms); 156, Copulatory spines (Csp); 157, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 158, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947913/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947895>
    dc:description "FIGURES 95–101. D. foveicollis. Male. 95, Head and pronotum. Foretibiae showing the spines (Sp) on internal margin and pad (Fos); 96, Apical half of foretibia; 97, Spines on foretrochanter (Tsp) and base of internal margin of forefemur (Fsp); 98, Metasternum; 99, Copulatory spines (Csp); 100, Detail of left paramere. Female. 101, Genitalia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947895/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947921>
    dc:description "FIGURES 163–165. D. sulcicollis. Male. 163, Copulatory spines (Csp); 164, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 165, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947921/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947917>
    dc:description "FIGURES 159–162. D. sulcata. Male. 159, Apical half of foretibia showing the spines (Sp) on internal margin and pad (Fos); 160, Copulatory spines (Csp); 161, Punctures on dorsal surface on pygophore (PP); 162, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947917/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947875>
    dc:description "FIGURES 43–47. Species of genus Dilasia. 1. 43, D. ashlocki Female, allotype (2.24 mm); 44, D. carvalhoi Female, holotype (2.24 mm); 45, D. colludens Male (2.27 mm); 46, D. crassicornis Male holotype; 47, D. gracilicornis Male paratype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947875/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947883>
    dc:description "FIGURES 60–72. Dilasia crassicornis. Male. 60, Head, 61, Pronotum; 62, Foretibia showing pad (Fos) and row of spines (Sp); 63, Pad; 64, Foretrochanter showing spines (Tsp); 65, Hemelytron; 66, Sternum and base of abdomen showing metasternum (Ms); 67, Copulatory spines (Csp); 68, Pygophore; 69, Detail of processus penniformis (Prp) on aedeagus; 70, Detail of punctures on dorsal surface on pygophore (PP); 71, Detail of left paramere; 72, Prominence on pygophore beneath the paramere (Pro)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947883/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947881>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–59. Dilasia colludens. Male. 56, Detail of left paramere (LP). Female. 57, Head and pronotum; 58, Metasternum; 59, Genitalia showing the parietovaginal gland (PG)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947881/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947891>
    dc:description "FIGURES 86–94. Species of genus Dilasia. 2. 86, D. foveicollis Male; 87, Idem. Male, holotype (1.75 mm); 88, D. fuscula Female, syntype (2.83 mm); 89, D. galateae; 90, D. microps; 91, Idem. Female holotype (2.53 mm); 92, D. neotropicalis Female holotype (2.65 mm); 93, D. punctipennis (2.56 mm); 94, Idem. Male holotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947879>
    dc:description "FIGURES 50–55. Dilasia carvalhoi. Male. 50, Fore leg; 51, Foretibia showing the row of spines (Sp) in the inner margin; 52, Metasternum; 53, Pygophore; 54, Detail of punctures on pygophore (PP) visible from above; 55, Detail on left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947879/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947925>
    dc:description "FIGURES 166–169. D. unicolor. Male. 166, Copulatory spines (Csp); 167, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 168, Detail of processus penniformis (Prp) on aedeagus; 169, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947925/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947911>
    dc:description "FIGURES 145–148. D. reuteri. Male. 145, Copulatory spines (Csp); 146, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP) and processus penniformis (Prp) on aedeagus; 147, Detail of processus penniformis; 148, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947911/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947889>
    dc:description "FIGURES 79–85. D. gracilicornis. Male. 79, Head and pronotum; 80, Foretibia showing a reduced pad (Fos) and the row of spines (Sp) on internal margin; 81, Apex of foretibia; 82, Hemelytron; 83, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternum (Ms); 84, Copulatory spines (Csp); 85, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947889/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947927>
    dc:description "FIGURES 170–173. D. varicolor. Male. 170, Copulatory spines (Csp); 171, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 172, Detail of processus penniformis (Prp) on aedeagus; 173, Detail of left paramere." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4947927/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947901>
    dc:description "FIGURES 113–123. D. microps. Male. 113, Head; 114, Pronotum; 115, Foretibia showing the spines (Sp) on internal margin and pad (Fos); 116, Apical half of foretibia; 117, Spines on foretrochanter (Tsp); 118, Sternal area showing the metasternum (Ms); 119, Copulatory spines (Csp); 120, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 121, Detail of left paramere. Female. 122, Genitalia; 123, Detail of punctures (Pfg)." ;
